A summary of plague in Zambia
-----------------------------
Until the current outbreak, plague had been endemic [in the Southern
Province (Namwala District) [of Zambia. No cases were reported [from 1954
to 1985; 1 (nonfatal) in 1986; 0 [from1987 to 1995.
319 cases of bubonic plague (26 fatal) were reported [from December 1996
to February 1997 from Namwala District. No cases were reported in 1998; 0
in 1999.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The current outbreak is in the Eastern Province. - Mod.ES
